raw_data.description: Works directly with client to identify models, goals and expected management outcomes; designs and test statistical models and statistical analysis plans; performs data validation, test for bias, evaluates data and makes judgments for addressing missing or outlying data, conducts data analysis and prepares data summaries, identifying assumptions made, and all possible interpretations, and limitations of the results.

raw_data.title: Study Coordinator
raw_data.description: Coordinates and administers research study associated activities. Assists in project planning, and ensures that pre- established work scope, study protocol, and regulatory requirements are followed. Recruits and coordinates research subjects, as appropriate, and serves as principle administrative liaison for the project. Oversees and coordinates the provision of administrative and staff services to director the investigators; develops and maintains recordkeeping systems and procedures.

raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert
raw_data.description: Provides expert consultation on integrating strategic Human Resources, Legal, and Scientific Services, General Management, and IT solutions across multiple domains such as financial, human capital, legal, training, scientific, behavioral health, and IT fields. Leads intricate business and operational projects, develops programs and training in human capital, finance, legal representation, and scientific services. Manage complex, sensitive projects, sets project goals, produces detailed documents, and stays current on relevant laws and regulations.

raw_data.title: Technical Analyst
raw_data.description: Provides support with research analysis and integration, scientific review, and technical writing, preparation of scientific reports and briefing presentations. Provides technical expertise, leadership, and project coordination services to support and maintain continuity of the organizations systems and networks. Assists with research program planning, development, and evaluation to meet programmatic objectives, mission, and initiatives. Assist with the organization, writing, and editing of complex and highly specialized technical research documents such as annual reports, and research publications.

raw_data.title: Time and Attendance Analyst
raw_data.description: Conducts and reports time and attendance audits. Assist with the daily maintenance and administration of the system. Assist with corrections to individual records and program requirements to ensure proper duty assignments and compensation. Facilitates and implements electronic form and signature processes. Aides in the training for supervisors, managers, and employee.

raw_data.title: Unarmed Security Guard
raw_data.description: Unarmed security guards are responsible for following detailed instructions and procedures to ensure that any security breaches or emergencies are quickly discovered and reported to the appropriate authority. Their primary duty is to observe and report any security or emergency situations. The guard is responsible for enforcing regulations and procedures designed to prevent security breaches and exercising judgment and discretion when responding to incidents and emergencies. Depending on the severity of the situation, they must decide whether to intervene directly, ask for assistance, keep the situation under control or surveillance, or report the incident or situation to the appropriate authority. Guards undergo training in methods and techniques for protecting controlled areas and must meet physical fitness standards.

raw_data.title: Urinalysis Specialist/Site Coordinator
raw_data.description: Conduct on-site and off-site random drug testing of employees; Coordinate with Government personnel in the assignment and prioritization of requested work; Coordinate the activities of, and provide oversight of, the collection staff during the on-site collection process; Plan and reserve trips to the selected testing sites; Educate supervisors and employees concerning the federal Drug-Free Workplace Programs (DFWP)s and applicable regulations, as required; Ensure that custody control forms (CCF) are completed in compliance with client guidelines; Ensure that specimens and associated CCFs are shipped to client’s designated laboratory within 24 hours of collection; Ensure that the Medical Review Officer (MRO) copy of the CCFs and essential documents are shipped to the MRO within 24 hours of the collection; Report insufficient specimens and refusals to the client and to the MRO, in accordance with Mandatory Guidelines; Enter data obtained from the specimen collection and coordination into HR computer systems; Ensure that all laptops are password protected and stored in secure location in accordance with client Sensitive Systems Policy Directives; Testify in court proceedings to support the government; Maintain the confidentiality of employees’ Personal Identifiable Information (PII) and report all breaches or unauthorized disclosure of such to the appropriate officials in accordance with client Safeguarding Sensitive Personally Identifiable Information; and; Attend scheduled meetings called by client Officials at on-site locations and or via teleconference.

raw_data.title: Web Developer
raw_data.description: Designs, develops, and maintains internal and external websites and cloud platforms. Uses knowledge of common web development languages to build and expand site functionality. Creates and enhances overall website appearance using design software and design designs site navigation that is clear and easy to understand. Ensures sites remain scalable while complying with performance and security standards. Updates site content based on input from marketing and documents changes in source code.
